SIMPLE: subscribe
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subscribe
<hw>Sub*scribe"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Subscribed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Subscribing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>subscribere</ets>, <ets>subscriptum</ets>; <ets>sub</ets> under +
<ets>scribere</ets> to write: cf. F. <ets>souscrire</ets>. See
<er>Scribe</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To write underneath, as one's
name; to sign (one's name) to a document.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[They] <qex>subscribed</qex> their names under them.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir T. More.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To sign with one's own hand; to give consent to, as
something written, or to bind one's self to the terms of, by writing
one's name beneath; <as>as, parties <ex>subscribe</ex> a covenant or
contract; a man <ex>subscribes</ex> a bond</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the bishops <qex>subscribed</qex> the sentence.</q>
<rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To attest by writing one's name beneath; <as>as,
officers <ex>subscribe</ex> their official acts, and secretaries and
clerks <ex>subscribe</ex> copies or records</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To promise to give, by writing one's name with the
amount; <as>as, each man <ex>subscribed</ex> ten dollars</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To sign away; to yield; to surrender.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>To declare over one's signature; to publish.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Either or must shortly hear from him, or I will
<qex>subscribe</qex> him a coward.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subscribe</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Subscribe
<hw>Sub*scribe"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To sign one's
name to a letter or other document.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To give consent to something written, by signing
one's name; hence, to assent; to agree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So spake, so wished, much humbled Eve; but Fate⟦br⟧
<qex>Subscribed</qex> not.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To become surely; -- with <xex>for</xex>.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To yield; to admit one's self to be inferior or in
the wrong.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will <qex>subscribe</qex>, and say I wronged the duke.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To set one's name to a paper in token of promise to
give a certain sum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>To enter one's name for a newspaper, a book,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subscriber</ent>⟦br⟧
